{
  "text": "The findings indicate that nurses that were successful in their career possessed five elements of career success: they (a) provided high-quality care, (b) were exemplary employees, (c) embarked on lifelong professional development, (d) displayed positive personal attributes, and (e) felt internally satisfied. These are dividable into further 14 subthemes (Fig. 1) . Our findings, thus, support work of others, who argued and found that career success was a multidimensional concept [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "55367967",
